    "name": "HT-MC-BTC-CLM-CSH-AllocDrift-LiqBuffer-6m0",
    "description": "ACTUS Hybrid Treasury v2: Semantic Fix — CSH for LiquidityBuffer\n\nFIX: LiquidityBufferModel detached from CLM (BTC position) and\nreattached to a proper CSH (Cash) contract representing fiat reserves.\n\nPrevious bug: LB was attached to CLM, treating BTC lending principal\n($2M) as 'cash balance'. This caused cascading depletion:\n  $2M → $1.3M → $591K → $165K → $0 in 4 months.\nLB was draining the BTC position to 'replenish' a fictional cash\nshortfall, while AllocationDrift tried to buy back BTC (tug-of-war).\n\nFix: Separate concerns correctly:\n  CLM (BTC)  → AllocationDriftModel only (monitors BTC allocation %)\n  CSH (fiat) → LiquidityBufferModel only (monitors cash buffer health)\n  PAM (T-bills) → no behavioral models (deterministic maturity)\n\nCSH contract represents the $500K operational cash reserve.\nLB parameters scaled to match: minBuffer=$200K, targetBuffer=$350K.\nLB reads actual fiat NP, compares against projected outflows, and\nsignals T-bill liquidation only when the REAL cash position is short.\n\nCross-contract cash flow: ACTUS contracts are independent. BTC sale\nproceeds (CLM PP payoff) do not automatically increase CSH NP.\nHowever, both models read shared reference indexes. In production,\nPORTFOLIO_TOTAL_VALUE would be updated between simulation runs to\nreflect actual cash position changes.\n\nPortfolio (6 contracts):\n  Contract 1: CLM  — 40 BTC ($2M @ $50K) lent at 3% APY\n  Contract 2: CSH  — $500K operational fiat cash reserve\n  Contract 3: PAM  — T-Bill #1 $500K, matures Mar 31\n  Contract 4: PAM  — T-Bill #2 $500K, matures May 31\n  Contract 5: PAM  — T-Bill #3 $250K, matures Jun 30\n  Contract 6: PAM  — T-Bill #4 $500K, matures Jul 31",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
